<i>adverb</i>: 훤히 [훤ː히], 환히 [환ː히], 섬세히 [섬세히] <br>
<ul style="list-style-type:square">
<li><i>adverb</i><br>
<dt>훤히 [훤ː히]</dt><br>
<dd>1. brightly; lightly</dd><br>
<dd>조금 흐릿할 정도로 밝게.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of being slightly, dimly bright.</dd><br>
<dd>2. openly; clearly</dd><br>
<dd>앞이 탁 트여 매우 넓고 시원스럽게.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of view being sweeping and unobstructed.</dd><br>
<dd>3. clearly; obviously</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 일의 내용이나 사정이 확실하고 분명하게.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of something being transparent, obvious or quite predictable.</dd><br>
<dd>4. attractively; finely; handsomely</dd><br>
<dd>외모가 잘생겨 보기에 매우 시원스럽게.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of having an extremely pleasing, neat, attractive appearance.</dd><br>
<dd>5. clearly; exactly; well</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 일이나 대상에 대해 잘 알고 있는 상태로.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of having an accurate and deep knowledge about a certain task or object.</dd><br>
<dt>환히 [환ː히]</dt><br>
<dd>1. brightly; radiantly</dd><br>
<dd>빛이 비치어 맑고 밝게.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of being very clear and bright as light shines.</dd><br>
<dd>2. openly; clearly</dd><br>
<dd>앞이 탁 트여 넓고 시원스럽게.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of something imparting a feeling of not being confined, because it has an open view.</dd><br>
<dd>3. clearly; obviously</dd><br>
<dd>무슨 일이 되어 가는 사정이나 속내가 분명하게.</dd><br>
<dd>In the manner of the progress or intention of a certain event being clear.</dd><br>
<dd>4. attractively; finely; neatly</dd><br>
<dd>얼굴이 깔끔하게 잘생겨 보기에 좋게.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of having a pleasing, neat, and attractive appearance.</dd><br>
<dd>5. brightly; beamingly; radiantly</dd><br>
<dd>표정이나 성격이 명랑하고 밝게.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of one's face or personality being bright and cheerful.</dd><br>
<dt>섬세히 [섬세히]</dt><br>
<dd>1. finely</dd><br>
<dd>곱고 가늘게.</dd><br>
<dd>Finely and thinly.</dd><br>
<dd>2. accurately</dd><br>
<dd>매우 자세하고 꼼꼼히.</dd><br>
<dd>In great detail and accuracy.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>